This document is an "IBM Batch Report" PDF, dated June 15, 2016, detailing the processing of Batch Number 13 from the 'Bangor' Vote Collection Point (ID 2178) within Electoral Event ID 19694 for New South Wales. It lists 50 individual ballots, identified by "Ballot Number" and "Ballot ID", and reports the outcome of numerous ballot processing checks.

For each of the 50 ballots, the report provides statuses for checks including 'QualityAssurance Checked', 'Initials Checked', 'Official Mark Checked', 'UnusualMarkings Checked', 'Formality Result Checked', 'Verification Action', 'Formality Reason Checked', and various 'ATL' (Above The Line) and 'BTL' (Below The Line) preference and formality checks (e.g., 'ATL Preferences Checked', 'ATL Mismatches', 'BTL Preferences Checked', 'BTL Mismatches').

The relevance to the FOI request [LEX540] is direct: this document is a specific example of the "IBM Outputs" and "IBM Batch Report" files from 2016 that were sought. It provides granular insight into the ballot processing, including batch metadata and ballot-level check outcomes, as outlined in the request overview. Uniquely, for all 50 ballots detailed in this particular report, every processing check, including those frequently noted as having "HAS ISSUES" in the request overview (such as `UnusualMarkings Checked`, `Verification Action`, `Formality Reason Checked`, `ATL Mismatches`, and `BTL Mismatches`), is marked "OK", indicating successful processing without any identified anomalies or exceptions for this specific batch.
